Proposed pipeline for lithium–ion RUL prediction.

To enhance optimization stability and reproducibility, the TLSTM/CNN weights are initialized using a clustering-based DE method (left of the figure). DE samples a population in weight space, clusters candidates, and initiates backpropagation from the optimal member of the dominant cluster, therefore expediting convergence and diminishing vulnerability to suboptimal initializations. In compliance with the reviewer’s request, the diagram distinctly identifies the battery type (Li–ion cylindrical 18,650) and the individual NASA PCoE units utilized (B0005/B0006/B0007/B0018), elucidating the scope and enabling transfer to alternative chemistries and datasets. Table 1 shows the symbols and notations used in this study.Table 1
